com.github.mlaursen.database.managers

Class ObjectManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.mlaursen.database.managers.ObjectManager
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    TestingObjectManager

    public class ObjectManager
extends java.lang.Object
    THe Object Manager class generates the packages and procedure for the database objects given. THe object manager does NOT create these packages and procedures in the database. It is expected that a DBA or someone else has created these packages/procedures.
    Author:
    mlaursen

      • delete

        public <T extends DatabaseObject> boolean delete(T object)
        Deletes a Database Object from the database. It checks if there is a package for the database object and if that package includes a delete procedure. If it does and the primary key is not null, the stored procedure is executed.
        Parameters:
        object - The object to delete from the database
        Returns:
        True if at least 1 row was deleted from the database
